    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240\u00b0C/ 220\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>waxy</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces, then add them to a pot with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cover them with<strong> boiled water</strong> and cook over a medium heat for 10-15 min or until tender, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cod-with-speedy-herby-hollandaise-and-crushed-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>shredded kale</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cod-with-speedy-herby-hollandaise-and-crushed-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>dill </strong>finely</p><p>Reboil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cod-with-speedy-herby-hollandaise-and-crushed-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!), reserve the pot for later</p><p>Gently crush the <strong>potatoes</strong> with a fork, season them with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and sprinkle over the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>and <strong>sliced shallot</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>potatoes </strong>with<strong> olive oil</strong> and give everything a good mix-up, then put the tray[s] in the oven for 10 min or until the potatoes are starting to crisp</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cod-with-speedy-herby-hollandaise-and-crushed-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>shredded kale </strong>to the reserved pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook them for 3-4 min or until they're tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cod-with-speedy-herby-hollandaise-and-crushed-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Pat your<strong> cod fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>cod</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it's opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cod-with-speedy-herby-hollandaise-and-crushed-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the fish is cooking, melt 40g <span class=\"text-purple\">[60g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[80g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> in a pot over a low heat</p><p>Once melted, remove the pot from the heat and add your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> Dijon mustard </strong>and <strong>chopped dill</strong></p><p>Whisk until you have a thick sauce<strong> </strong>then season with<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>\u2013<strong> </strong>this is your <strong>speedy</strong> <strong>herby hollandaise</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cod-with-speedy-herby-hollandaise-and-crushed-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cod</strong> with the <strong>crushed potatoes</strong> and<strong> shredded kale</strong> to the side</p><p>Spoon the<strong> speedy herby hollandaise </strong>over the cod</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
